						<summary>King Kulottuṅga Cōḻa gives endowment to a high-status <foreign>pāṇaṉ</foreign> for appointment of <foreign>pāṇars</foreign> to sing to Lord of Tiruviṭaimarutūr–for which he received <foreign>kāṇi</foreign>–and to train temple dancers (<foreign>taḷiyilār</foreign> and <foreign>tēvaraṭiyār</foreign>), for which he received gold, paddy and a house.
